declarations.comments:
Create a React component from a _specification_ of that component.

A _specification_ consists of a state type, an initial value for that state,
a function to apply incoming props to the internal state, and a rendering
function which takes props, state and a state update function.

The rendering function should return a value of type `JSX`, which can be
constructed using the helper functions provided by the `React.Basic.DOM`
module (and re-exported here).
declarations.title: react

declarations.comments:
Create a stateless React component.

Removes a little bit of the `react` function's boilerplate when creating
components which don't use state.
declarations.title: stateless

declarations.comments: Create a `JSX` node from a React component, by providing the props.
declarations.title: createElement

declarations.comments:

For more information see: https://reactjs.org/docs/reconciliation.html#keys
declarations.title: createElementKeyed

declarations.comments: Render an Array of children without a wrapping component.
declarations.title: fragment

declarations.comments:
Render an Array of children without a wrapping component.

Provide a key when dynamically rendering multiple fragments along side
each other.
declarations.title: fragmentKeyed

modules.name: React.Basic.DOM
modules.comments:
This module defines helper functions for creating virtual DOM elements
safely.

Note: DOM element props are provided as records, and checked using `Union`
constraints. This means that we don't need to provide all props, but any we
do provide must have the correct types.

declarations.comments: Create a text node.
declarations.title: text

declarations.comments: An abstract type representing records of CSS attributes.
declarations.title: CSS

declarations.comments:
Create a value of type `CSS` (which can be provided to the `style` property)
from a plain record of CSS attributes.

E.g.

```
div { style: css { padding: "5px" } } [ text "This text is padded." ]
```
declarations.title: css

declarations.comments: Standard props which are shared by all DOM elements.
declarations.title: SharedProps

modules.name: React.Basic.DOM.Events
modules.comments: This module defines safe event function and property accessors.

declarations.comments:
An event handler, which receives a `SyntheticEvent` and performs some
effects in return.
declarations.title: EventHandler

declarations.comments: Event data that we receive from React.
declarations.title: SyntheticEvent

declarations.comments: An _actual_ DOM node (not a virtual DOM element!)
declarations.title: DOMNode

declarations.comments: The underlying browser Event.
declarations.title: DOMEvent

declarations.comments:
Encapsulates a safe event operation. `EventFn`s can be composed
to perform multiple operations.

For example:

```purs
input { onChange: handler (preventDefault >>> targetValue)
                    \value -> setState \_ -> { value }
      }
```
declarations.title: EventFn

declarations.comments:
Create an `EventHandler`, given an `EventFn` and a callback.

For example:

```purs
input { onChange: handler targetValue
                    \value -> setState \_ -> { value }
      }
```
declarations.title: handler

declarations.comments:
Merge multiple `EventFn` operations and collect their results.

For example:

```purs
input { onChange: handler (merge { targetValue, timeStamp })
                    \{ targetValue, timeStamp } -> setState \_ -> { ... }
      }
```
declarations.title: merge
